# Phase 1: Analyze the Fix

This is a patch for LoopVectorize:

[LV] Support interleaving with conditional scalar assignments
This extends the existing support to work with arbitrary interleave factors. The main change here is reworking the ExtractLastActive VPInstruction to take a variable amount of arguments and handling it in unrollRecipeByUF and VPInstruction::generate.

The select condition for all mask/data values in a find-last recurrence is the true if the mask for any part is true. Because of this the masks for inactive parts will be updated to all-false when the parts with active lanes are updated. This ensures the mask/data for last active element always corresponds to the greatest part with an active lane.

This means finding the last element in the middle block simply requires chaining the `extract.last.active` to forward the result from the last active part through any inactive parts ahead of it. 
