1493   // The reduction using MinOrMaxPhiR needs adjusting to compute the correct
1494   // result:
1495   //  1. Find the first canonical indices corresponding to partial min/max
1496   //     values, using loop reductions.
1497   //  2. Find which of the partial min/max values are equal to the overall
1498   //     min/max value.
1499   //  3. Select among the canonical indices those corresponding to the overall
1500   //     min/max value.
1501   //  4. Find the first canonical index of overall min/max and scale it back to
